T1  - On the Caterer Problem
AU  - Prager, William
Y1  - 1956/10/01
PY  - 1956
DA  - 1956/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.3.1.15
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.3.1.15
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 15
EP  - 23
VL  - 3
IS  - 1
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In the present paper, the Caterer Problem is shown to be equivalent to a Hitchcock Distribution Problem [Hitchcock, F. L. 1941. The distribution of a product from several sources to numerous locations. J. Math. Phys. 20 224?230.] with a very special cost matrix. For the case q = p ? 1, a simple procedure taking advantage of this fact is developed and shown to yield Jacobs' solution. The possible extension of the procedure to the case p ? q > 1 is illustrated by a numerical example.
AB  - In the present paper, the Caterer Problem is shown to be equivalent to a Hitchcock Distribution Problem [Hitchcock, F. L. 1941. The distribution of a product from several sources to numerous locations. J. Math. Phys. 20 224?230.] with a very special cost matrix. For the case q = p ? 1, a simple procedure taking advantage of this fact is developed and shown to yield Jacobs' solution. The possible extension of the procedure to the case p ? q > 1 is illustrated by a numerical example.
